******
[1] Norovirus, hospital - UK (England, Staffordshire): suspected
Date: Fri 9 Apr 2004
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@ntlworld.com>
Source: BBC News online, Thu 8 Apr 2004 [edited]
<http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/staffordshire/3611093.stm>

England: Outbreak of Gastroenteritis in Staffordshire Hospital
-----------------------------------------------
A severe [viral infection] causing sickness and diarrhea is affecting
patients and staff at a Staffordshire hospital. Patients on 1/4 of the
wards at the University Hospital of North Staffordshire have been affected
by the 48-hour viral infection. Cleaning procedures have been stepped up,
and restricted admission is in place.
Medical specialists at the hospital have been advising patients, staff, and
visitors about precautions that can be taken to prevent the virus from
spreading. Visitors are being told to stay at home if they display any
symptoms. Dr. John Gray, a consultant microbiologist, says the illness has
been affecting people across all of north Staffordshire. Controlling the
disease in a closed community, like a hospital, can be extremely difficult,
he said.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
