[2] Rotavirus, contaminated cucumbers - Russia (Yoshkar Ola)
Date: Tue 13 Apr 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Regions.ru, Regional News Agency, Fri 9 Apr 2004
[translated by Mod.NR, edited]
<http://www.regions.ru/newsheadlines/index.html?section=news&topic=health>

Russia: Rotavirus Infection in Yoshkar Ola attributed to Contaminated
Cucumbers
-----------------------------------------------
During the 1st quarter of 2004 an outbreak of rotavirus infection occurred
in the city of Yoshkar-Ola [Mari El administrative district]. According to
the City Epidemiological Surveillance Center, 83 percent of the 73 cases
were children under the age of 2. The source of infection was discovered to
be fresh cucumbers, which were sold by a mini-market in Heroes [of the
battle of Stalingrad] Street.
The 1st signs of this infection were diarrhea, malaise, abdominal pain, and
fever. Epidemiologists are asking parents to be careful with feeding
children. All fruits and vegetables should be washed thoroughly, especially
during the flood season.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The advice to wash fruit and vegetables carefully may not be sufficient to
control the outbreak if the public water supply, or agricultural irrigation
systems, are vulnerable to fecal contamination during flooding. - Mod.CP]
